    "To be precise, our denoising model G requires the input of not only the source image x and the noisy target image y t, but also the latent variable Z (Z ∼ N(0, I))) and t (t ∼ U(1, T)).",
    "During training, our goal is to minimize the adversarial loss, as demonstrated in Eq. 10, which is comparable to the one presented in the previous section.",
    "To express our loss in a different form, we have rephrased it in Eq. 20 by applying the equivalent transformation of L as detailed in Appendix A of DDPM 14.",
    "The adversarial loss D adv in GAN can be formulated using different types of divergence measures, such as KL divergence, Jensen-Shannon divergence, and others 36.",
    "However, for this particular case, the f-divergence has been chosen."
